data.title: Family Birthday Meal
data.text: Just discovered this place and was told it has been there for years. It has something for everyone. Great Sushi and teriyaki.

data.title: So good!
data.text: Huge sashimi, very fresh, and some of the best rolls that we've had in a long time. Our toddler threw rice everywhere and they were extremely sweet and understanding. Definitely recommend

data.title: Typically Good Food
data.text: We order food to go all the time and it's usually very good.  Sushi as well as Teriyaki.  This last time the food was not so good, not sure if there was a chef in training or what happened.  We will try them again because they usually have very good food and I am hopeful that this last time was a fluke.

data.title: Very Goog Nigiri
data.text:
For lunch time the place seemed dark and as much like a '50s diner as a Sushi place, but the waitress was warm and welcoming.  A small bowl of miso soup and a small plate of edamame came with the menu, which was nice.

The nigiri prices seemed high for "one piece" but in fact the pieces of precisely cut fish that came with the special nigiri lunch were more than twice the size of sashimi cuts I've had elsewhere, so in the end represented good value.  I particularly like that the little dipping bowls, wasabi, pickled ginger, and soy sauce were all in containers already at the table you may concoct your own sauce to your own taste.  

In my experience nigiri comes with the fish (etc) draped over and pressed into sushi rice.  My lunch came on a flat wooden "boat" with two slabs each of three (chef's) choices of excellent sashimi attractively assembled and the rice in a ball at the end.  Fine with me, but different than my expectations.  

I didn't think the hot sake was particularly good for the price, but it complemented the food as hot sake does.

data.title: Good food, a little pricey on sushi
data.text:
This was a lovely establishment. Looked family run, and they were great with checking up on us during the meal.

The sushi was a bit pricey, but the traditional Japanese food was normally priced. They offered bento boxes, sushi, teriyaki, but no yakasoba. They did offer ramen and mochi.

I would visit this restaurant again.

data.title: Very Good Food at a reasonable price
data.text: We visited this place in October 2014 - My friend who lives in Seattle recommended it.  I enjoy sushi, my daughter does not.  My sushi, the Lion King Roll, was outstanding!!  The miso soup to start the meal was wonderful!  My daughter tried the Chicken and it was great! Reasonable price, decent atmosphere and good service. I would try it again!

data.title: delish!
data.text: This place is so great.  Fresh, delicious, beautifully presented sushi.  Not like the conveyor belt places.  They bring you a little miso soup & edamame while you're waiting.  And they finish it off with the cutest little orange with a toothpick umbrella. My husband is not a sushi kind of guy & he says their teriyaki is very good too.   I go for lunch frequently.  It is so reasonably priced too.  The sushi is just as good as Trappers but less expensive.  I say GO!
